1
00:00:00,253 --> 00:00:03,904
"Fruit"

2
00:00:04,035 --> 00:00:06,552
(Five years later)

3
00:00:07,315 --> 00:00:10,902
(Episode 10: Fruit)

4
00:00:28,300 --> 00:00:29,583
Please stamp this for me first.

5
00:00:29,583 --> 00:00:31,200
- Thank you.
- Okay, no problem.

6
00:00:46,400 --> 00:00:48,005
Come to the art room?

7
00:01:21,173 --> 00:01:22,173
Miss.

8
00:01:23,200 --> 00:01:24,466
You're here.

9
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:30,900
I came back to get my diploma.

10
00:01:31,500 --> 00:01:32,500
And also...

11
00:01:33,900 --> 00:01:35,466
to visit the school.

12
00:01:42,366 --> 00:01:43,600
Five years.

13
00:01:44,866 --> 00:01:46,600
Time flies so fast.

14
00:01:47,568 --> 00:01:48,568
Yeah.

15
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:51,100
Sometimes,

16
00:01:51,966 --> 00:01:54,433
I still find myself looking for

17
00:01:55,166 --> 00:01:57,100
a familiar face in the crowd.

18
00:02:03,412 --> 00:02:04,412
Then...

19
00:02:06,699 --> 00:02:08,200
did you find it?

20
00:02:12,719 --> 00:02:13,719
No.

21
00:02:18,266 --> 00:02:19,700
Because that face...

22
00:02:21,366 --> 00:02:23,266
only existed five years ago.

23
00:02:36,333 --> 00:02:37,466
I'm sorry.

24
00:02:39,966 --> 00:02:41,366
Back then...

25
00:02:42,500 --> 00:02:44,300
I didn't say goodbye to you properly.

26
00:02:51,966 --> 00:02:53,266
It's all in the past.

27
00:02:59,533 --> 00:03:00,800
This spot...

28
00:03:02,566 --> 00:03:04,433
doesn't seem to have changed at all.

29
00:03:10,700 --> 00:03:12,300
Because there are some marks

30
00:03:13,866 --> 00:03:15,700
that the soul always remembers.

31
00:03:16,800 --> 00:03:17,766
Then...

32
00:03:21,652 --> 00:03:23,085
this mark...

33
00:03:28,400 --> 00:03:30,033
must be really important?

34
00:03:36,533 --> 00:03:37,866
What do you think?

35
00:04:16,133 --> 00:04:17,500
These past years...

36
00:04:18,666 --> 00:04:20,700
I've learned to let drawings speak.

37
00:04:22,700 --> 00:04:24,233
They are more honest than I am.

38
00:04:25,666 --> 00:04:27,200
And braver than I am.

39
00:04:37,726 --> 00:04:38,726
Then...

40
00:04:42,800 --> 00:04:45,166
is there one about me?

41
00:05:15,500 --> 00:05:16,666
These past years...

42
00:05:17,533 --> 00:05:19,300
I kept wondering

43
00:05:19,966 --> 00:05:21,266
if that fruit...

44
00:05:22,366 --> 00:05:24,066
might not be me.

45
00:05:34,533 --> 00:05:36,300
Fruit grows on its own.

46
00:05:37,133 --> 00:05:40,166
We just used five years to irrigate it.

47
00:05:47,300 --> 00:05:48,566
And now...

48
00:05:50,066 --> 00:05:51,766
we've both grown up.

49
00:06:04,866 --> 00:06:06,900
I'm thankful that we both grew up well.

50
00:06:11,326 --> 00:06:12,351
Miss.

51
00:06:12,351 --> 00:06:13,351
Hmm?

52
00:06:14,766 --> 00:06:16,033
I really...

53
00:06:16,866 --> 00:06:17,900
really...

54
00:06:18,800 --> 00:06:20,600
really missed you.

55
00:06:23,008 --> 00:06:24,008
Yeah.

56
00:06:25,246 --> 00:06:26,246
Me too.

57
00:06:32,366 --> 00:06:33,674
Miss.

58
00:06:33,674 --> 00:06:34,674
Hmm?

59
00:06:35,570 --> 00:06:37,178
Your heart is beating so fast.

60
00:07:03,366 --> 00:07:06,533
Fruit isn't just the result.

61
00:07:06,533 --> 00:07:09,900
It's the proof of light and time interchanged.

62
00:07:09,900 --> 00:07:12,300
They sprout in waiting,

63
00:07:12,300 --> 00:07:14,466
bloom in suppression.

64
00:07:14,466 --> 00:07:17,266
Until the moment fate meets again,

65
00:07:17,266 --> 00:07:19,300
ther realization hits...

66
00:07:19,300 --> 00:07:21,100
Those heartbeats

67
00:07:21,100 --> 00:07:24,771
finally grew into the fruit in the heart.

68
00:07:24,771 --> 00:07:28,122
(The end)

69
00:07:28,122 --> 00:07:30,514
(There will be a little surprise tomorrow!)
